  <h2>What It Actually Means to Sell to a Cash Buyer</h2>
  <p>When you sell to a cash buyer, you're cutting out the part of the process that makes traditional home sales slow and uncertain. No bank needs to approve the loan. No appraiser needs to agree with the price. No buyer needs to sell their own house first. The sale either happens or it doesn't — and when it does, it closes fast.</p>
  <p>I've bought houses all over Wichita — east side, west side, Derby, Andover, Haysville, El Dorado. The common thread isn't the neighborhood, it's the seller's situation. People who need to close quickly, or don't want to deal with repairs, or have inherited a property they don't want to manage. A cash sale solves all of those problems at once.</p>

